comment: Tarski's system uses the weaker ~ ax6v instead of the bundled ~ ax-6 , so here we show that the degenerate case of ~ ax-6 can be derived. Even though ~ ax-6 is in the list of axioms used, recall that in set.mm, the only statement referencing ~ ax-6 is ~ ax6v . We later rederive from ~ ax6v the bundled form as ~ ax6 with the help of the auxiliary axiom schemes. (Contributed by NM, 23-Apr-2017.)
